Cell.Text: [S] Thank you dear. It took time for someone to pick up the soulgem. I am eternally grateful to you.

[S] Uh oh, in such shape you are. Sadly I cannot help you at this stage. Draw breath and I will let you be informed. | I am.. or you could say I was Tara Winter-Owl. I helped court mage Fonsvis Nuleendis in experiment and it did not go how was expected. | Now we have limited time. As you are heading to the same fate that was written to me.
By touching the soulgem you have released the same curse upon yourself that haunted me.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_TaraIntroduction02: What do you mean what have you done to me?

Cell.Text: *sighs* Dear girl. I am not sure how to tell this to you. | When Fonsvis cured my eternally sore head something happened to me. | When it started my body became very sensitive. After few days it was already almost impossible for me to think clearly. | Then it became impossible for me to think anything else than intimacy.

It was such tragedy. Eventually I lost all control and could not resist men that attended to me. | They became jealous to each other then one of them confronted the other. | When they fought Fonsvis fleed but Badkvir Boulder-Robber died. Sweet Badkvir he was good to me.

During the confrontation Fonsvis mentioned something about Sanguine being responsible of all of this. | Fonsvis had also hidden notes of his doings with sanguine to this room. I came to them at the time I did not understand what it meant. | I could still gather enough of my mind to address Sanguine. I begged him to release me of the curse. | I could not do anything else. This basement has been somehow separated of the castle. I tried yelling and it did not help.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_TaraIntroduction05: What happened to you? Were you trapped to the soulgem?

Cell.Text: [S] *nods* now dear we need to find help. Sanguine also needs to explain his doing. | Fonsvis had hidden book that contained information how to contact sanguine. I found it. It should still be here.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_TaraIntroduction06: Someone had sealed the basement with a spell. It was impossible to find in.

Cell.Text: [S] Thats sad to hear. Please don't leave me like this. If you find anything please return to me.
[S] G|Thank you, thank you! Of course, please catch your breath and relax. | Hopefully with this, we gain Sanguines favor and he will help us both.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_TaraIntroductionAccept: If you let me a moment. I will help you. It was quite an experiment

Cell.Text: Yes.. Sanguine is indeed a daedric prince. I prayed for Talos and he did not answer. Sanguine listened to me.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_WhoIsSanguineTopic: Isn't Sanguine a daedric prince? Is it safe to contact him?

Cell.Text: Fonsvis was court mage at the time. I used to have these awful headaches. Fonsvis promised to relieve of them. | Not all went as he promised and here we are.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_WhoIsFonsvisTopic: You mentioned Fonsvis Nuleendis. Who is he?

Cell.Text: [S] They were men from the court. I don't know them. I am sure you can find out more when you talk to the people of the keep.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_QuestionOthers: Who were the others you mentioned?

Cell.Text: Yes, poor Badkvir. He was so nice to me. He was the servant that mainly looked after me. There were only few people that knew I was here. | Fonsvis casted his magics on him and I saw Badkvir burn alive. After that Fonsvis closed the hatch and he did not come down here anymore. | Then I became desperate. So exhausted of hunger and lust I had to do something. So I contacted Sanguine.

Node.Caption: MoaH_IntroductionQuest_WhoIsBadkvirBoulderRobberTopic: Are those Badkvirs bones on the floor? How did this happen?
